The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 10 January is 26,067 (3,017.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 05 January, there were 6,094 new confirmed cases (705.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 29 December, there were 4,170 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 46% (1,924 extra cases).
